    {
      "id": "ab77d4c6fc75bf855f4ffb86b03d516398736cc6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-18 17:34:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\ncan we add a description of the race that this patch is trying to fix. Currently it explains the change without explaining the race.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "09bf547d827ad7a6d031256e9799d2e81305cd2d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-18 17:37:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "99b08430489751198a7d9665fd67254a9acbe8e9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 470,
        "name": "Olaf Weber",
        "email": "olaf.weber@hpe.com",
        "username": "olaf"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-20 08:20:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nWould this be a good description?\n\nThe changes made for Multi-Rail introduce a race in the LNet shutdown\npath. The code keeps two states in the_lnet.ln_shutdown: 0 means LNet\nis either up and running or shut down, while 1 means LNet is shutting\ndown. In lnet_select_pathway(), if we need to restart and drop and\nrelock the lnet_net_lock we can find that LNet went from running to\nstopped, and not tell the difference.\n\nReplace...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "7aff7e6af634134657029c0c472803ecfedbbf05",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2016-10-21 21:08:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI would be interested to know why it was introduced and the impact of that race condition on behavior. Just makes it easier for people to get context without having to spend a lot of time in the code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
